<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1069">
You are given a DNA sequence: a string consisting of characters A, C, G, and T. Your task is to find the longest repetition in the sequence. This is a maximum-length substring containing only one type of character.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line contains a string of $n$ characters.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the length of the longest repetition.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 10^6$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>ATTCGGGA</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>3</code>    </div>
